result.execSummary:
The defendant Carneth J Brown was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Paid in Adams County - Adams County forward check to Marquette County

Defendant Carneth J Brown in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz and Intern Josh Andresen.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states plea agreement.  Court questions Atty Hendee regarding the traffic tickets.  Atty Hendee states that they have not been discussed as part of the agreement; however, the State moves to dismiss both traffic tickets 15TR902 & 903.  Mr. Andresen agrees.  Defendant agrees and enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty.
15TR902 & 15TR903 to be dismissed.

Intern Mr. Andresen makes a statement to the court and asks the court to follow the joint recommendation.

BY THE COURT:  Court orders 5 days in the Marquette County Jail
Credit = 5 days
Time Served
Court Costs = $243.00
15TR902 & 15TR903 to be dismissed.

  Defendant agrees to the $15.00 payment plan fee.
Payment Plan:  $50.00/month commencing in September
Criminal Complaint served on Defendant at the Marquette County Jail 06-08-15 per MASO

with conditions:
*Absolute Sobriety; zero tolerance
*No possession or consumption of any intoxicants
*Not to go on any premises that sells/serves alcohol unless it is for employment purposes

BY THE COURT:  Court enters a Not Guilty plea on behalf of the defendant.
Set for Return.
Defendant is to speak with the PD office.

Defendant Carneth J Brown in court, in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Defendant received a copy of the criminal complaint & waives it's reading.   Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.    Atty Hendee has no objection to a signature bond with conditions.
Defendant agrees with the bond request.

BY THE COURT:  Court sets a $500 Signature bond with conditions:
*Absolute Sobriety; zero tolerance
*No possession or consumption of any intoxicants
*Not to go on any premises that sells/serves alcohol unless it is for employment purposes

  Return date scheduled for August 5, 2015 at 02:30 pm.
